{{see|algebra|Algebra|àlgebra}}
==Spanish==

===Etymology===
From Arabic {{ARchar|[[جبر|الجبر]]}} (al-jabr) “reunion”, “resetting of broken parts”, used in the title of [[w:Al-Khwarizmi|al-Khwarizmi]]’s influential work {{ARchar|علم الجبر والمقابلة}} (ilm al-jabr wa’l-muqābala), “the science of restoration and equating like with like”

